  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat the oven to 160°C/320°F."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the dukkah, toast all of the nuts separately (almonds: 8-10 mins, hazelnuts: 10-12mins, pistachios: 8-10 mins, sesame seeds: 6-8 mins)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dry toast the coriander, fennel and cumin seeds separately in a pan. Toast for a few minutes each on medium heat until they begin to smell aromatic."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Grind the herbs in a spice grinder or pestle and mortar."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pulse the nuts in a small food processor until you have a chunky crumb, take care not to over process into a powder- you should have large pieces of nuts."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the seeds to the nuts and season with salt to taste. Add the aleppo pepper here if you’re using it."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the tomatoes and lay them flat on a plate. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle a few tablespoons of dukkah and finish with some basil leaves. Enjoy!"
    }
  ],
